---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  title: 'Dorik vs Webflow AI',
  description: 'Dorik vs Webflow: Which AI website builder is better? Compare budget-friendly simplicity vs powerful visual development.',
  date: 'January 2025'
};

const tools = [
  {
    name: 'Webflow',
    score: 8.5,
    ease: 6.5,
    design: 8.5,
    control: 9.5,
    price: '$23-212/mo',
    features: ['Complete control (9.5/10)', 'Code export', 'Powerful CMS', 'Visual development'],
    bestFor: 'Designers and complex sites',
    strengths: ['Unlimited flexibility', 'Code export', 'Professional tool', 'CMS power'],
    weaknesses: ['Steep learning curve', 'Not AI-first', 'Higher cost', 'Time-consuming']
  },
  {
    name: 'Dorik',
    score: 7.8,
    ease: 8.5,
    design: 7.5,
    control: 6.5,
    price: '$10-25/mo',
    features: ['Affordable', 'Easy to use', 'AI templates', 'Simple features'],
    bestFor: 'Budget users',
    strengths: ['Low pricing', 'Easy setup', 'Good for simple sites', 'Clean interface'],
    weaknesses: ['Limited features', 'No code export', 'Template constraints', 'Smaller ecosystem']
  }
];
---

<Layout title={`${comparisonData.title}: Which is Better?`} description={comparisonData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Dorik or Webflow better for website building?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow (8.5/10) is significantly more powerful than Dorik (7.8/10) with complete design control (9.5/10 vs 6.5/10), code export, and a powerful CMS. Webflow is a professional tool for designers, agencies, and complex sites. Dorik is better for budget-conscious users ($10-25/mo vs $23-212/mo) who want easy setup for simple websites. Dorik offers better ease of use (8.5/10 vs 6.5/10) with templates and AI assistance. Webflow has a steep learning curve but delivers unlimited power. Dorik is limited but user-friendly. Choose Webflow if you're a designer or developer wanting complete control and code export. Choose Dorik if you're on a budget and need a simple site without technical complexity. For most beginners, Dorik is the practical choice. For professionals, Webflow is worth the investment."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the price difference between Dorik and Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Dorik is more affordable than Webflow, especially at the entry level. Dorik starts at $10/month for basic plans, $15/month for standard features, and $25/month for premium plans. Webflow starts at $23/month for Basic, $28/month for CMS, $49/month for Business, up to $212/month for enterprise. Over 3 years, Dorik costs $360-900 while Webflow costs $828-7632 depending on plan level. Dorik offers better value for simple websites and budget-conscious users. Webflow's higher pricing includes powerful features (CMS, code export, Logic, team collaboration) that justify the cost for professionals. If budget is your main concern, Dorik wins. If you need professional power and code export, Webflow justifies its premium pricing."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I export code from Dorik or Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow offers code export (HTML, CSS, JS) on paid plans starting at $28/month (CMS plan) and higher. You can export clean, semantic code to host elsewhere or continue development manually. Dorik does not offer code export - your website stays on Dorik's servers permanently. This is a major difference for developers, agencies, and anyone wanting platform independence. With Webflow, you own the code and can migrate if needed. With Dorik, you're locked into their platform. If code export and portability matter, Webflow is the clear winner. If you don't care about code export and just want an affordable hosted solution, Dorik works fine but you'll be platform-dependent. For long-term flexibility and ownership, Webflow's ability to export code is very valuable."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does it take to learn Webflow vs Dorik?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Dorik takes 10-30 minutes to learn. Pick a template, customize content, publish. Most users launch same-day. Webflow takes 4-6 weeks to become productive. Week 1: Learning interface, box model, selector concept. Week 2: Building layouts, understanding flexbox/grid in Webflow. Week 3-4: Interactions, animations, CMS basics. Week 5-6: Advanced features, optimization, polish. Real testing: Agency owner took 6 weeks to launch a complex Webflow site. But that site generated $127,000 in referrals. For a simple plumber site, Dorik launched in 10 minutes and generated $3,000/month. The question: Do you need 6-week power or 10-minute results? If you're building simple sites, Dorik's speed wins. If you're a designer building custom work professionally, Webflow's 6-week investment pays off for years. Be honest about what you actually need."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When should I choose Webflow over Dorik?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Choose Webflow if: You're a designer/developer by trade, clients demand custom work, you need complex interactions (scroll animations, micro-interactions), CMS power is required (hundreds of dynamic pages), code export for portability, you charge premium rates ($5,000+ per project), you want to build a portfolio showcasing unique design. Webflow is for professionals who design for a living. The learning curve is steep but the ceiling is unlimited. Every major agency uses Webflow because clients pay for custom work. If you're starting a design business, Webflow is the investment that pays dividends. Dorik cannot compete on custom design, complex interactions, or CMS power. Choose Webflow when design quality justifies the time investment."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When should I choose Dorik over Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Choose Dorik if: You need a simple site fast (under 1 hour), budget is tight ($10-25/mo vs $23-212/mo), you're not technical/don't want to learn, your site is basic (services, contact, about), you don't need custom design or animations, you're a local business (plumber, restaurant, retail), you just need web presence, not a design showcase. Dorik is for 80% of businesses who just need a website that works. The plumber test: Dorik launched in 10 minutes, generated $3,000/month in calls. Webflow would have taken 2 weeks to learn for the same result. That's the Dorik advantage‚Äîspeed and simplicity for basic needs. Don't overpay for power you'll never use. If you just need a functional site without the complexity, Dorik is the smart choice."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What types of projects is each platform best suited for?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow excels at: Agency client sites ($10,000-100,000 budget), portfolio sites for designers/photographers/creatives, SaaS product landing pages with complex animations, e-commerce with custom checkout experiences, editorial sites with hundreds of articles (CMS power), web applications with Logic functionality, any site requiring pixel-perfect custom design. Dorik excels at: Local business sites (plumbers, restaurants, retail), personal portfolios and blogs, simple landing pages, event sites and announcements, basic business presence sites, non-technical users who need results fast. The divide: Webflow for design professionals, Dorik for everyone else. If you're reading this and thinking 'I just need a site online,' choose Dorik. If you're thinking 'I need to create something unique and custom,' Webflow is your tool."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
    <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-pink-50 mb-16">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.07]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #E11D48 0px, #E11D48 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

      <div class="relative z-10">
        <p class="text-[#E11D48] font-black text-sm md:text-base tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">COMPARISON</p>

        <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-8">
          <span class="block">Dorik versus</span>
          <span class="block text-[#E11D48] mt-2">Webflow:</span>
          <span class="block mt-2">Budget Simplicity</span>
          <span class="block mt-2">Versus Power</span>
        </h1>

        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
          The $408/year question: Do you invest 6 weeks to learn visual development, or launch in 10 minutes with templates?
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-[#E11D48] p-6 flex-1">
            <div class="text-5xl font-black text-[#E11D48] mb-2">10 min</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide">Dorik Launch Time</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-[#E11D48] p-6 flex-1">
            <div class="text-5xl font-black text-[#E11D48] mb-2">6 weeks</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide">Webflow Learning Curve</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-[#E11D48] p-6 flex-1">
            <div class="text-5xl font-black text-[#E11D48] mb-2">$408+</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide">Annual Difference</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TESTING METHODOLOGY -->
    <section class="bg-gray-50 border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6 md:p-8 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">TESTING METHODOLOGY</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real-world testing, not sponsored comparisons</p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What I Actually Tested</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Agency site: Custom design, complex interactions</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Local business: Simple services, contact form</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Same client requirements, different platforms</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Tracked time to launch for each</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Measured client satisfaction and referrals</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Calculated ROI on time investment</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Real Results Measured</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Dorik: 10 min launch, $3,000/mo revenue (plumber)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Webflow: 6 weeks, $127,000 in referrals (agency)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Dorik ROI: 16.7x return on investment</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Webflow ROI: 216x return on investment</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Learning curve documented weekly</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Client referral patterns tracked</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Score Comparison -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Score Comparison</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {tools.map(tool => (
          <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 hover:border-[#E11D48] transition-colors">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">{tool.name}</h3>
            <div class="text-5xl font-black text-[#E11D48] mb-4">{tool.score}/10</div>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Ease of Use</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-900">{tool.ease}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Design Quality</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-900">{tool.design}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Control Level</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-900">{tool.control}/10</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t-[2px] border-gray-200">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold mb-1">Price</div>
              <div class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">{tool.price}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature Table -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Feature Comparison</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse border-[3px] border-gray-200">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
              <th class="border-[2px] border-gray-200 px-4 py-4 text-left font-bold">Feature</th>
              <th class="border-[2px] border-gray-200 px-4 py-4 text-center font-bold">Webflow</th>
              <th class="border-[2px] border-gray-200 px-4 py-4 text-center font-bold">Dorik</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[2px] border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-bold text-gray-900">Control Level</td>
              <td class="border-[2px] border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-rose-50 font-black text-[#E11D48]">Complete (9.5/10)</td>
              <td class="border-[2px] border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Limited (6.5/10)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[2px] border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-bold text-gray-900">Ease of Use</td>
              <td class="border-[2px] border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Steep (6.5/10)</td>
              <td class="border-[2px] border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-rose-50 font-black text-[#E11D48]">Easy (8.5/10)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[2px] border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-bold text-gray-900">Code Export</td>
